    <item>
      <title>Bamboo Fun Pen on Ubuntu 12.04 Precise Pangoline</title>
      <link>https://www.zybnet.com/2012/10/29/bamboo-fun-pen-on-ubuntu-12-04-precise-pangoline/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 29 Oct 2012 17:39:23 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>raffaeleSgarro@gmail.com (Raffaele Sgarro)</author>
      <guid>https://www.zybnet.com/2012/10/29/bamboo-fun-pen-on-ubuntu-12-04-precise-pangoline/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The driver is supplied by &lt;a href=&#34;https://launchpad.net/~lekensteyn/+archive/wacom-tablet&#34;&gt;this PPA&lt;/a&gt;, so:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo add-apt-repository ppa:lekensteyn/wacom-tablet
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install wacom-dkms
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then we need a program to draw: &lt;a href=&#34;http://mypaint.intilinux.com/&#34;&gt;MyPaint&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo apt-get install mypaint mypaint-data
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Happy drawing! :)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
